## How to Run

### Backend
```bash
cd backend
npm install
# Ensure .env has valid MONGO_URI
npm start
# For verification: node verify_api.js
```

### Frontend
```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
# Open http://localhost:5173
```

### AI Service
```bash
cd ai-budget-assistant
python app.py
```

## Troubleshooting
> [!WARNING]
> **MongoDB Authentication Failed**: The provided credentials or IP whitelist for MongoDB Atlas seem incorrect. Update [backend/.env](file:///d:/projects/shubkar/backend/.env) with a valid `MONGO_URI`.

> [!WARNING]
> **PowerShell Security Error**: If you see `npm : File ... cannot be loaded because running scripts is disabled`, it is a Windows permissions issue.
> **Fix**: Run the command using `cmd` instead of PowerShell, OR run `node server.js` directly instead of `npm start`.

